name: PlayStreamEvents
description: Entity profiles are the top level containers for essentially all information about an entity.
apiDescriptionList: Entity profiles are the top level containers for essentially all information about an entity.

EntityKey.name: EntityKey
EntityKey.description: Entity identifier class that contains both the ID and type.

properties.name: Type
properties.description: Entity type. Optional to be used but one of EntityType or EntityTypeString must be set.

properties.name: TypeString
properties.description: Entity type. Optional to be used but one of EntityType or EntityTypeString must be set.

properties.name: EventNamespace
properties.description: The namespace in which the event is defined. It must be prepended with 'com.playfab.events.'

properties.name: OriginalId
properties.description: The original unique identifier associated with this event before it was posted to PlayFab. The value might differ from the EventId value, which is assigned when the event is received by the server.

properties.name: OriginalTimestamp
properties.description: The time (in UTC) associated with this event when it occurred. If specified, this value is stored in the OriginalTimestamp property of the PlayStream event.

properties.name: Payload
properties.description: Arbitrary data associated with the event. Only one of Payload or PayloadJSON is allowed.

properties.name: PayloadJSON
properties.description: Arbitrary data associated with the event, represented as a JSON serialized string. Only one of Payload or PayloadJSON is allowed.

properties.name: Events
properties.description: Collection of events to write to PlayStream.

properties.name: AssignedEventIds
properties.description: The unique identifiers assigned by the server to the events, in the same order as the events in the request. Only returned if FlushToPlayStream option is true.

calls.name: WriteEvents
calls.summary: Write batches of entity based events to PlayStream.
